current_text: "Whoever gets him, they'll be getting a good one," David Montgomery said. INDIANAPOLIS — Hakeem Butler has been surrounded by the supportive presence of his former Iowa State teammate, David Montgomery. Montgomery's comment, "Whoever gets him, they'll be getting a good one," reflects his high regard for Hakeem Butler’s abilities on the football field. This statement came around the time when both players were entering the NFL, showcasing the camaraderie and mutual respect that can develop between college teammates. Hakeem Butler, known for his impressive size, catching radius, and athleticism, had made a significant impact as a wide receiver at Iowa State, which had many looking forward to his potential performance in the NFL. David Montgomery, on his part, has been recognized for his work ethic and skills as a running back, further emphasizing the weight of his endorsement of Butler. The sentiment shared by Montgomery highlights the strong bond and support system that often forms among teammates, extending beyond their college years and into their professional careers.
